                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-01-28</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I'm about to begin my first documentary film project and though I'm working with a skilled filmmaker I need all the help I can get. <P>In preparation I read, "Making Documentary Films and Reality Videos" by Barry Hampe. This book covers A-Z regarding documentary filmmaking and to boot, it's a great read! Within the first few pages, my thoughts on how documentary film is made were quashed and replaced with new and correct information. Mr. Hampe draws from personal experiences which are cited throughout, and this makes the book read a bit like a story, not so much like a dry textbook. I zipped right through it, learned a tremendous amount, and have pages marked for future reference. Thank you Mr. Hampe!</span>
                  
              
